<ServicePage
  title="Tooth-Colored Fillings in Bayside, Queens NY | Thrive Dental"
  description="Natural-looking composite fillings in Bayside, Queens NY. We replace old metal fillings with tooth-colored restorations that blend seamlessly. Call (718) 225-6677."
  category="Restorative Dentistry"
  categoryHref="/services/restorative-dentistry"
  h1="Tooth-Colored Fillings in Bayside, NY"
  subtitle="Modern composite fillings are strong, durable, and virtually invisible. We use natural-colored resin that blends with your tooth — no more silver spots when you smile."
  heroImg={heroImg}
  overviewTitle="Strong restorations that look like nothing is there."
  overviewText="Composite (tooth-colored) fillings are made from a blend of glass particles and acrylic resin that bonds chemically to the tooth structure. Unlike old amalgam (silver) fillings — which were packed into a prepared cavity and held in place mechanically — composite bonds directly to the tooth, which means less healthy structure needs to be removed to place it. The resin is shade-matched to your tooth, applied in layers, and hardened with a curing light. The finished restoration is smooth, natural-looking, and functional from the moment you leave."
  overviewExtra="At Thrive Dental in Bayside, we no longer place silver amalgam fillings. Every cavity we treat is restored with tooth-colored composite, and we're happy to replace old metal fillings for patients who want a more natural appearance or are concerned about the mercury content in traditional amalgam. Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck come to us specifically to have old metal work replaced — and the visual difference is immediate. We use rubber dam isolation during composite placement to ensure a moisture-free bond, which significantly extends the longevity of the restoration. If you have a cavity, catch it now: small fillings take 20–30 minutes and cost a fraction of the crown or root canal a neglected cavity eventually requires."
